            <div class="col-xs-offset-1 col-xs-10 col-xs-offset-1"> <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#demo4">4.	What Is Alcohol Myopia? </button>
                <div></br></div>
  <div id="demo4" class="collapse">
      
      <div>				
      				 <p>Have you ever wondered why alcohol affects people
						differently? And why some people are affected differently from one
						time to the next? Alcohol, for example, can sometimes make people
						hostile and aggressive, and at other times friendly and warm; it
						can relieve tension and anxiety and yet at other times increase
						irritability and stress. 
						</p><p>
						One model for understanding these
						differences is that alcohol intoxication leads to a myopia in our
						ability to perceive and process information. "Myopia" means
						nearsightedness, which causes people to have trouble seeing things
						off in the distance or off to the side. Alcohol intoxication seems
						to produce nearsightedness in our thinking: alcohol makes our
						world smaller by reducing our awareness of what is happening
						around us when we drink. The more you drink the less aware you
						become.
						</p><p>
						When sober, people typically think quickly, drawing on
						lots of information. Laboratory studies on alcohol have shown that
						heavy drinking limits our ability to think and our awareness of
						what is happening around us. Like nearsightedness, alcohol causes
						us to only see what is happening right in front of us right now.
						Alcohol does not allow us to think about complex things when we
						are intoxicated.
						</p><p>
						Alcohol myopia helps explain how alcohol can
						cause a person to feel happy one time and angry the next, and how
						good friends can end up in fights. Alcohol seems to magnify our
						emotions, and myopia helps us believe things that are not real.
					</p>
		</div>
      <div>
      <img src="resources/images/alcohol4.jpg" class="img-rounded" alt="Cinque Terre" width="90%" height="65%">
          </div>
      
   
  </div>
